<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="580" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.458/34: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the Shah of Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reza Shah
                                Pahlavi</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-13">March 13, 1938</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>It affords me great pleasure to extend to Your Majesty cordial
                                birthday greetings and my sincere best wishes for a long, happy and
                                prosperous reign.</p>
                            <p>With the near approach of the Iranian New Year festivities, I
                                likewise wish to express the hope that the coming year will witness
                                the strengthening of those close bonds of friendship which for so
                                long have united the American and Iranian peoples.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin D.
                                Roosevelt</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>